SIMPLE: lopsided
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lopsided
<hw>Lop"sid`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lop</ets> +
<ets>side.</ets> Cf. <er>Lobsided</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Leaning
to one side because of some defect of structure; <as>as, a
<ex>lopsided</ex> ship</as>.</def> <rj><au>Marryat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unbalanced; poorly proportioned; having much more on
one side than the other; -- also used metaphorically; <as>as, a
<ex>lopsided</ex> victory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Full of idiosyncrasies.</def> <rj><au>J. S.
Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lopsided victory</ent>⟦br⟧
